Conducting manyGLMs with the full community matrix

manyGLM wouldnt run unless the factors were converted to a dummy variable

Run the nested model

# Run nested model
m4 <- manyglm(comm.mat.mv ~ predictors$TREATMENT + (1|predictors$BLOCK/seeds$DATE.FACT), 
              family = "negative_binomial")

plot(m4)

anova(m4, p.uni = "adjusted")

Model for seed richness time series

First calculate richness

Plot distribution

# Plot distribution
plotdist(seeds$RICH, histo = TRUE, demp = TRUE)

descdist(seeds$RICH, discrete=TRUE, boot=500) # NB

## summary statistics
## ------
## min:  0   max:  5 
## median:  0 
## mean:  0.385

## estimated skewness:  2.791148 
## estimated kurtosis:  12.35535

Run model

m6 <- glmmTMB(RICH ~ TREATMENT + (1|BLOCK/DATE),
              data = seeds, family = nbinom2(link = "log"))
sim_m6 <- simulateResiduals(fittedModel = m6, n = 250)

car::Anova(m6)
